==English==
===Etymology===
The plant common name is derived from the [[Christian]] [[tradition]] figure, presumably at least partly from the tendency of those [[plant]]s to spread through a [[garden]] (ie. [[wander]])..
===Proper noun===
# A [[Jewish]] [[shoemaker]] who, in [[Christian]] tradition, taunted [[Jesus Christ]] on the way to his (Jesus') [[crucifixion]] and for that was [[condemn]]ed to [[wander]] the [[Earth]] until Jesus' return (ie. the [[second coming]]).
[[Category:Christianity]]
# One of three species of [[spiderwort]] plants, ''Tradescantia pallida'' (also called ''Setcreasea purpurea''), ''Tradescantia fluminensis'', and ''Tradescantia zebrina''.
